1
00:00:00,834 --> 00:00:03,437
Knuckle: ’cause i--

2
00:00:03,470 --> 00:00:06,206
I can’t see him

3
00:00:06,240 --> 00:00:08,776
as just something
to exterminate now.

4
00:00:10,077 --> 00:00:11,245
You heard him.

5
00:00:11,278 --> 00:00:13,714
He acknowledged
how serious we were.

6
00:00:13,747 --> 00:00:16,450
He wasn’t a bad guy.

7
00:00:16,483 --> 00:00:18,285
( Moans )

8
00:00:18,318 --> 00:00:21,488
So why would we keep doing this?

9
00:00:21,522 --> 00:00:24,592
I can’t think of a reason.

10
00:00:24,625 --> 00:00:26,093
Knov: The king.

11
00:00:26,126 --> 00:00:29,096
The soldiers
are of no consequence.

12
00:00:29,129 --> 00:00:31,264
The king can just wave his hand

13
00:00:31,298 --> 00:00:33,767
and turn all of them
into evil spawn.

14
00:00:35,135 --> 00:00:36,103
♪

15
00:00:36,136 --> 00:00:38,071
( Singing in Japanese )

16
00:01:19,546 --> 00:01:21,481
♪

17
00:01:25,252 --> 00:01:27,187
( Wind blowing )

18
00:02:33,253 --> 00:02:36,690
Netero: This is a test site
for military weapons...

19
00:02:38,959 --> 00:02:42,463
Which means that we won’t need
to restrain ourselves.

20
00:02:51,004 --> 00:02:52,939
King: Why do you and I
have to fight?

21
00:02:52,973 --> 00:02:54,641
Netero: Huh?

22
00:02:54,675 --> 00:02:58,646
King: You have absolutely
no chance of defeating me.

23
00:02:58,679 --> 00:03:02,383
There is no need for us
to hasten your inevitable death.

24
00:03:07,588 --> 00:03:11,225
Netero: Saying I can’t win
is pretty presumptuous of you.

25
00:03:11,258 --> 00:03:14,495
I can tell that you
don’t know squat about me.

26
00:03:14,528 --> 00:03:15,462
( Blows )

27
00:03:16,864 --> 00:03:20,267
If you judge a book
by its cover,

28
00:03:20,300 --> 00:03:22,936
don’t be surprised
if you get burned.

29
00:03:22,970 --> 00:03:25,539
King: You’ve got it wrong.

30
00:03:25,572 --> 00:03:28,608
You don’t seem
like some ordinary man

31
00:03:28,642 --> 00:03:30,878
who can’t read
the state of the battle.

32
00:03:32,679 --> 00:03:37,350
I was born for one reason,
and that is to rule this world.

33
00:03:37,384 --> 00:03:39,887
Originally you pathetic humans

34
00:03:39,920 --> 00:03:42,389
were no more
than livestock to me,

35
00:03:42,422 --> 00:03:44,925
but i’ve changed my mind.

36
00:03:48,362 --> 00:03:51,632
I have since determined
that there are a few humans

37
00:03:51,665 --> 00:03:53,534
that are worth keeping alive...

38
00:03:54,668 --> 00:03:56,837
Like that girl, for example.

39
00:04:01,308 --> 00:04:04,578
You are worthy as well.
I can sense it.

40
00:04:06,613 --> 00:04:08,815
If you will back down
this instant...

41
00:04:09,950 --> 00:04:12,352
Then I will consider
sparing you.

42
00:04:18,492 --> 00:04:20,427
Netero: You’re saying
you would spare me

43
00:04:20,460 --> 00:04:22,462
and not the others?
Is that right?

44
00:04:25,365 --> 00:04:26,900
♪

45
00:04:26,934 --> 00:04:29,804
Given my unique position,

46
00:04:29,837 --> 00:04:32,473
I simply can’t accept
that offer.

47
00:04:42,683 --> 00:04:45,019
Narrator: Meanwhile,
deep within the palace,

48
00:04:45,052 --> 00:04:48,789
in exchange for his agreement
to stay still for the moment,

49
00:04:48,822 --> 00:04:50,357
pouf was pressing pitou

50
00:04:50,390 --> 00:04:53,026
to explain exactly
what had happened.

51
00:04:53,060 --> 00:04:55,062
♪

52
00:05:07,674 --> 00:05:09,543
( No audible dialogue )

53
00:05:09,576 --> 00:05:11,812
Pitou complied
with pouf’s request,

54
00:05:11,845 --> 00:05:14,481
telling him
what happened after the attack

55
00:05:14,515 --> 00:05:17,551
and all that had transpired
since they had separated.

56
00:05:19,953 --> 00:05:22,956
Pitou made it a point
to include several details

57
00:05:22,990 --> 00:05:26,527
that gon did not know
to ensure that gon’s attention

58
00:05:26,560 --> 00:05:28,829
would be focused
on the explanation.

59
00:05:30,764 --> 00:05:34,601
But pitou, unable to describe
the events accurately,

60
00:05:34,635 --> 00:05:38,472
chose not to mention
how the king had held komugi,

61
00:05:38,505 --> 00:05:41,842
not knowing how to capture
the scene in words.

62
00:05:49,783 --> 00:05:52,853
There was
no significant change in gon.

63
00:05:55,689 --> 00:05:56,623
However...

64
00:05:58,091 --> 00:06:00,860
When gon’s eyes
wavered briefly,

65
00:06:00,894 --> 00:06:03,897
pitou knew the plan
had been a success.

66
00:06:07,868 --> 00:06:09,503
Neferpitou: The king...

67
00:06:10,904 --> 00:06:12,072
He left with the enemy

68
00:06:12,105 --> 00:06:14,908
of his own volition
by that doorway.

69
00:06:16,410 --> 00:06:18,746
There’s no need for us
to go after him.

70
00:06:20,514 --> 00:06:21,448
Shaiapouf: Hmm.

71
00:06:23,984 --> 00:06:25,786
I understand.

72
00:06:25,819 --> 00:06:27,788
He went south.

73
00:06:27,821 --> 00:06:29,923
Thank you for telling me.

74
00:06:31,024 --> 00:06:32,993
A fine play, pitou.

75
00:06:34,695 --> 00:06:38,532
Then we should stay here
and await his return.

76
00:06:39,600 --> 00:06:41,669
We must be patient.

77
00:06:46,773 --> 00:06:49,075
To maintain
only my outward appearance,

78
00:06:49,109 --> 00:06:52,079
I only need 1/7
of my flying segments.

79
00:06:56,617 --> 00:06:58,419
The other segments will go...

80
00:07:00,187 --> 00:07:01,955
To the king!

81
00:07:17,771 --> 00:07:20,474
King: You will fight
knowing that you cannot win?

82
00:07:22,576 --> 00:07:24,078
I don’t understand.

83
00:07:25,812 --> 00:07:28,448
Are you fighting me
for all of humanity?

84
00:07:28,482 --> 00:07:31,185
If so, then you should
know that my actions

85
00:07:31,218 --> 00:07:33,187
are entirely for their benefit.

86
00:07:36,890 --> 00:07:39,626
For example, in human society,

87
00:07:39,660 --> 00:07:43,063
lands are split by borders
marking their territory.

88
00:07:44,665 --> 00:07:46,567
On the right side of the border,

89
00:07:46,600 --> 00:07:48,502
children may starve to death,

90
00:07:48,535 --> 00:07:50,137
while on the left,

91
00:07:50,170 --> 00:07:53,840
idle dregs who do nothing
have everything they need.

92
00:07:54,908 --> 00:07:56,843
It’s absolute madness.

93
00:07:59,012 --> 00:08:01,448
I shall crush that madness

94
00:08:01,481 --> 00:08:07,087
and create a fair world
where the concept of inequality

95
00:08:07,120 --> 00:08:09,756
will be completely forgotten
for all time.

96
00:08:23,537 --> 00:08:24,571
Netero: Hmm.

97
00:08:25,873 --> 00:08:27,274
King: I don’t deny
that i’ll start

98
00:08:27,307 --> 00:08:31,211
by using power and terror
to accomplish my objective,

99
00:08:31,245 --> 00:08:33,914
but only when
absolutely necessary

100
00:08:33,947 --> 00:08:36,216
and only to bring about order.

101
00:08:36,250 --> 00:08:39,019
You see, I have learned

102
00:08:39,052 --> 00:08:41,621
what true power
is meant to be used for...

103
00:08:41,655 --> 00:08:42,789
( No audible dialogue )

104
00:08:45,225 --> 00:08:49,162
To protect the weak
who deserve to live.

105
00:08:49,196 --> 00:08:50,964
That is its purpose.

106
00:08:52,866 --> 00:08:56,036
Power shouldn’t be used
to torment the defeated.

107
00:08:56,069 --> 00:08:58,004
♪

108
00:09:03,810 --> 00:09:06,513
Netero: This is
quite the situation.

109
00:09:07,981 --> 00:09:09,883
King: I will not fight
with you now.

110
00:09:11,285 --> 00:09:14,255
I left the palace
so we could have a discussion.

111
00:09:15,923 --> 00:09:19,093
We need to have a free
and uninhibited conversation.

112
00:09:20,794 --> 00:09:23,830
Netero: Well,
he’s beginning to waver.

113
00:09:25,933 --> 00:09:27,735
King: Come closer.

114
00:09:27,768 --> 00:09:31,739
Netero: Wavering
between ant and human,

115
00:09:31,772 --> 00:09:35,743
yet it seems
he hasn’t yet realized

116
00:09:35,776 --> 00:09:38,812
that those two sides
are totally incompatible.

117
00:09:41,748 --> 00:09:45,318
And as of now,
neither one is dominant.

118
00:09:48,655 --> 00:09:51,124
He’ll fall to one or the other,

119
00:09:51,158 --> 00:09:54,561
but either way, the outcome
will remain the same.

120
00:09:56,230 --> 00:09:58,165
♪

121
00:10:00,734 --> 00:10:02,002
Man: We’re counting on you.

122
00:10:02,035 --> 00:10:05,138
You have only
one mission to carry out,

123
00:10:05,172 --> 00:10:08,842
the immediate execution of all
of these dangerous creatures.

124
00:10:10,711 --> 00:10:12,913
Netero: There have already
been many casualties.

125
00:10:14,748 --> 00:10:17,251
We will proceed
using any means necessary.

126
00:10:17,284 --> 00:10:19,319
Will that be acceptable to you?

127
00:10:19,353 --> 00:10:21,722
Man: Well, don’t ask me.

128
00:10:21,755 --> 00:10:25,058
We wouldn’t dream of telling
the experts how to proceed.

129
00:10:27,060 --> 00:10:30,030
All we desire now is
for those dangerous creatures

130
00:10:30,063 --> 00:10:33,833
to be eradicated as swiftly
and humanely as possible.

131
00:10:33,867 --> 00:10:36,670
Netero: Yes, of course.
I understand.

132
00:10:38,772 --> 00:10:41,275
So their goal
is to eradicate the ants,

133
00:10:41,308 --> 00:10:44,344
leaving the hunter association
to take the blame.

134
00:10:44,378 --> 00:10:45,880
I get it.

135
00:10:47,781 --> 00:10:49,983
( Wind blowing )

136
00:10:50,017 --> 00:10:52,887
I’m going to need
to make this fast...

137
00:10:53,987 --> 00:10:56,456
Before my heart is swayed.

138
00:11:03,063 --> 00:11:05,232
Look, king...

139
00:11:05,265 --> 00:11:07,300
We’ve all got problems,
you know.

140
00:11:08,368 --> 00:11:09,936
( King gasps )

141
00:11:09,970 --> 00:11:11,905
♪

142
00:12:16,470 --> 00:12:20,040
Netero:
100-type guanyin bodhisattva!

143
00:12:22,442 --> 00:12:24,311
First hand!

144
00:12:45,465 --> 00:12:47,400
( Wind blowing )

145
00:12:50,871 --> 00:12:53,407
( Wings fluttering )

146
00:12:54,608 --> 00:12:56,009
( Shaiapouf gasps )

147
00:12:57,144 --> 00:12:58,379
Is that...

148
00:12:58,412 --> 00:13:00,014
♪

149
00:13:03,317 --> 00:13:06,821
Menthuthuyoupi: I can’t sense
anyone else fighting here.

150
00:13:06,854 --> 00:13:09,357
Does that mean
that i’m the only one left?

151
00:13:11,091 --> 00:13:12,059
Shaiapouf: Youpi!

152
00:13:12,092 --> 00:13:13,827
Menthuthuyoupi: Huh? Huh?!

153
00:13:13,861 --> 00:13:19,266
Pouf! You’ve changed a lot
since the last time I saw you.

154
00:13:19,299 --> 00:13:22,803
Shaiapouf: I suppose I could
say the same thing about you.

155
00:13:24,371 --> 00:13:27,074
I had to be careful
and escape from there

156
00:13:27,107 --> 00:13:28,809
without alerting the enemy.

157
00:13:30,010 --> 00:13:31,979
If I moved
all my particles at once,

158
00:13:32,012 --> 00:13:34,581
it would have been suspicious,
so I moved slowly.

159
00:13:36,316 --> 00:13:37,551
I’m sure you’re rushed,

160
00:13:37,584 --> 00:13:39,886
but could you spare a moment?

161
00:13:39,920 --> 00:13:42,956
I need to tell you
what’s been happening.

162
00:13:45,626 --> 00:13:49,396
Menthuthuyoupi: Yeah.
I suppose i’ve got a minute.

163
00:13:49,429 --> 00:13:51,431
Guess everyone
does have their reasons.

164
00:13:51,465 --> 00:13:52,967
Shaiapouf: Uh...

165
00:13:55,669 --> 00:13:57,604
You sound so grown up.

166
00:14:04,244 --> 00:14:06,113
And there you have it.

167
00:14:07,581 --> 00:14:10,417
I hope pitou’s change
will benefit the king...

168
00:14:12,352 --> 00:14:14,254
But I can’t be sure.

169
00:14:14,288 --> 00:14:17,358
I’ve no conclusive proof
one way or the other.

170
00:14:19,526 --> 00:14:21,428
♪

171
00:14:28,468 --> 00:14:30,503
Narrator: Based on
his own experiences,

172
00:14:30,537 --> 00:14:34,174
youpi could understand
pitou’s behavior.

173
00:14:34,208 --> 00:14:35,476
- Shaiapouf: Youpi...
- Menthuthuyoupi: Eh?

174
00:14:36,677 --> 00:14:38,412
Shaiapouf: So tell me.

175
00:14:38,445 --> 00:14:40,948
What do you think
we should do now?

176
00:14:48,088 --> 00:14:49,489
Narrator: He was being tested.

177
00:14:50,958 --> 00:14:53,427
This tactic
made it quite clear to youpi

178
00:14:53,460 --> 00:14:57,664
that pouf was afraid,
unnerved by the subtle changes

179
00:14:57,698 --> 00:15:01,635
that both pitou and youpi
had only recently undergone.

180
00:15:05,339 --> 00:15:08,442
( Menthuthuyoupi scoffs )
A dumb question.

181
00:15:08,475 --> 00:15:09,543
( Grunts )

182
00:15:20,487 --> 00:15:22,956
♪

183
00:15:22,990 --> 00:15:25,459
There’s no time to waste.

184
00:15:25,492 --> 00:15:27,494
We must go to the king...

185
00:15:30,330 --> 00:15:33,133
And that’s all there is to it.

186
00:15:33,167 --> 00:15:34,669
Am I right?

187
00:15:34,701 --> 00:15:37,437
Narrator:
His response was sincere.

188
00:15:39,640 --> 00:15:41,475
Shaiapouf: Indeed, you are.

189
00:15:41,508 --> 00:15:44,444
Narrator: Only one thing
concerned him at the moment,

190
00:15:44,478 --> 00:15:47,314
and that was leaving
as quickly as possible...

191
00:15:50,184 --> 00:15:52,620
Because the fear
that gripped pouf

192
00:15:52,653 --> 00:15:55,156
had taken hold of youpi as well.

193
00:16:08,101 --> 00:16:10,036
♪

194
00:16:34,495 --> 00:16:37,498
Netero: I’m sure
that was a direct hit.

195
00:16:37,531 --> 00:16:39,099
He’s a tough one.

196
00:16:43,270 --> 00:16:45,005
King: A very good attack.

197
00:16:46,273 --> 00:16:48,408
I wasn’t expecting it.

198
00:16:48,442 --> 00:16:50,377
( Wind blowing )

199
00:16:52,246 --> 00:16:54,348
Are you satisfied?

200
00:17:01,655 --> 00:17:04,424
Netero: He still wants me
to sit with him?

201
00:17:07,227 --> 00:17:09,996
King: I will not repeat myself.

202
00:17:15,435 --> 00:17:17,370
♪

203
00:17:32,619 --> 00:17:34,754
Netero: Third hand!

204
00:17:43,163 --> 00:17:46,333
I cannot back down any longer.

205
00:17:51,305 --> 00:17:52,606
( Gasps )

206
00:17:54,308 --> 00:17:55,776
( Creaking )

207
00:17:55,809 --> 00:17:57,744
♪

208
00:18:00,681 --> 00:18:04,051
King: Are you really
so eager to die?

209
00:18:12,693 --> 00:18:14,328
Narrator:
From the king’s perspective,

210
00:18:14,361 --> 00:18:16,563
the wrath that was unleashed
was unimpressive,

211
00:18:16,597 --> 00:18:21,368
seemingly no stronger than that
of a child throwing a tantrum,

212
00:18:21,401 --> 00:18:25,171
but the king’s full power
was violent enough

213
00:18:25,205 --> 00:18:30,210
to make netero jump back more
than twice his usual distance.

214
00:18:31,912 --> 00:18:35,783
Netero couldn’t help but feel
insulted by this turn of events

215
00:18:35,816 --> 00:18:38,319
and by the fact
that his determination,

216
00:18:38,352 --> 00:18:42,223
strong as it was,
could be brushed off so easily.

217
00:18:46,894 --> 00:18:48,696
King: Wake up.

218
00:18:48,729 --> 00:18:53,500
Can’t you see words are all that
you and I will exchange here?

219
00:18:53,534 --> 00:18:55,503
You should save your energy.

220
00:18:57,571 --> 00:18:59,673
Netero: Damned newborn brat.

221
00:19:03,310 --> 00:19:06,747
If it were that simple,
I wouldn’t have to do this.

222
00:19:12,419 --> 00:19:13,353
Wait.

223
00:19:15,422 --> 00:19:18,725
Exchanging words?

224
00:19:22,396 --> 00:19:23,530
Hey, king...

225
00:19:25,799 --> 00:19:28,635
Would you like
to know your name?

226
00:19:31,371 --> 00:19:35,175
King: How is it that you have
come into possession of my name?

227
00:19:40,781 --> 00:19:42,650
Netero: Simple, really.

228
00:19:42,683 --> 00:19:46,387
My subordinates were present
at your mother’s deathbed.

229
00:19:47,721 --> 00:19:51,825
She uttered your name
with her dying breath.

230
00:19:51,859 --> 00:19:53,461
I bet i’m the only one

231
00:19:53,494 --> 00:19:56,497
who knows now those
same subordinates probably died

232
00:19:56,530 --> 00:19:58,432
fighting your royal guard.

233
00:19:58,465 --> 00:20:00,400
( Wind blowing )

234
00:20:04,505 --> 00:20:07,208
Are you interested
in fighting me now?

235
00:20:10,577 --> 00:20:12,312
I’ll make you a deal.

236
00:20:12,346 --> 00:20:14,415
If you can force me
to admit defeat,

237
00:20:14,448 --> 00:20:17,217
i’ll tell you your name.

238
00:20:19,553 --> 00:20:21,288
King: Force you?

239
00:20:21,321 --> 00:20:22,923
But without killing you?

240
00:20:22,956 --> 00:20:24,224
( Scoffs )

241
00:20:28,061 --> 00:20:30,864
So i’ll be playing
without a rook and bishop.

242
00:20:30,898 --> 00:20:32,867
♪

243
00:20:53,887 --> 00:20:57,491
Fine, then.
I’ll checkmate you shortly.

244
00:21:08,569 --> 00:21:10,871
♪

245
00:21:18,879 --> 00:21:20,381
♪

246
00:21:20,414 --> 00:21:21,916
Narrator: The real battle

247
00:21:21,949 --> 00:21:25,519
between netero and the king
has begun.

248
00:21:25,552 --> 00:21:27,487
( Singing in Japanese )

